Ohio State, Kansas, Duke, Pitt Selected as Top Seeds for NCAA Tournament

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-03-13T22:06:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-13/ohio-state-kansas-duke-pitt-selected-as-top-seeds-for-ncaa-tournament.html
  Ohio State University , the
University of Kansas, University of Pittsburgh and defending
champion  Duke University  were selected as top seeds for the
national menâ€™s college basketball tournament.   Ohio State (32-2) is the top overall seed after winning the
Big Ten Conference tournament for the second straight year. 
The Buckeyes hold the No. 1 spot in the East, one of four
regions in the National Collegiate Athletic Association
tournament, which this year has expanded to 68 teams from 65.  Kansas, which went 32-2 and captured the Big 12 tournament
title, claimed a No. 1 regional seed for the fourth time in five
years. Pittsburgh (27-5) is a top seed for the second time in
three years, while Duke gained a No. 1 regional seeding for the
12th time, one behind  North Carolina  for the second-most in NCAA
tournament history.  The NCAA tournament starts in two days in Dayton, Ohio,
with two of the four play-in games. Full tournament play begins
March 17-18 at eight sites. The championship game is scheduled
for April 4 at Reliant Stadium in Houston.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  